e wine professional.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSyrah (Wine). 0aWine and wine makingxHistory. 0aWine and wine makingzCalifornia. 0aWine and wine makingzRhône River Valley (Switzerland and France). 0aWine and wine makingzRhône River Valley (Switzerland and France). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  aaccessible.  aamerican wine.  abusiness owner.  acalifornia vineyard.  acalifornia wine.  acalifornia winery.  acoffee table book.  aeasy to read.  aeasy to understand.  afine wine.  ainspiring.  amotivational.  ared wine.  aresearch.  arhone variety.  arhone wine.  arhone.  ascholarly.  asmall business.  asuccess story.  asyrah.  atrue story.  avineyard.  awine book.  awine enthusiast.  awine grapes.  awine lover.  awine movement.  awine producers.  awine.  awinemakers.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052025666840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096514040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520965140423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520965140/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY